you know, had trained for,
had signed up for, and--

00:25:16.830 --> 00:25:18.630 align:middle line:84%
but they couldn't
get away from it.

00:25:18.630 --> 00:25:22.440 align:middle line:84%
And so that's one of the major
points of quantum physics

00:25:22.440 --> 00:25:27.210 align:middle line:84%
is that how do you factor in
consciousness into the equation

00:25:27.210 --> 00:25:29.156 align:middle line:90%
of the world and who we are?

00:25:29.156 --> 00:25:31.530 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Consciousness says--
all these physicists say,

00:25:31.530 --> 00:25:32.690 align:middle line:90%
is fundamental.

00:25:32.690 --> 00:25:33.490 align:middle line:90%
>> PAUL: Mhm.

00:25:33.490 --> 00:25:36.720 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: You know, you have
the notion of prima materia,

00:25:36.720 --> 00:25:40.210 align:middle line:84%
the soup, that's not in any
particular organized fashion.

00:25:40.210 --> 00:25:41.010 align:middle line:90%
>> PAUL: Right.

00:25:41.010 --> 00:25:41.843 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: The soup.

00:25:41.843 --> 00:25:43.590 align:middle line:90%
The chaos.

00:25:43.590 --> 00:25:46.890 align:middle line:84%
But consciousness has to be
applied to the chaos in order

00:25:46.890 --> 00:25:48.984 align:middle line:90%
for any creation.

00:25:48.984 --> 00:25:50.400 align:middle line:84%
And we're just an
example of that.

00:25:50.400 --> 00:25:52.108 align:middle line:84%
Everything we are,
everything we're doing

00:25:52.108 --> 00:25:55.230 align:middle line:84%
is just part of
that macro process.

00:25:55.230 --> 00:25:57.330 align:middle line:84%
Literally with every
thought of every day,

00:25:57.330 --> 00:25:59.887 align:middle line:84%
we're part of the
creative process, right?

00:25:59.887 --> 00:26:00.720 align:middle line:90%
>> PAUL: Yeah, yeah.

00:26:00.720 --> 00:26:02.511 align:middle line:84%
Well, the thing is--
so what you're saying,

00:26:02.511 --> 00:26:05.840 align:middle line:84%
what it brings to mind, from the
quantum physics point of view--

00:26:05.840 --> 00:26:07.380 align:middle line:84%
and keep in mind,
quantum physics,

00:26:07.380 --> 00:26:13.050 align:middle line:84%
it's being called the
greatest discovery in history,

00:26:13.050 --> 00:26:15.180 align:middle line:84%
in all of science,
and it's never

00:26:15.180 --> 00:26:17.520 align:middle line:90%
been proven wrong in one iota.

00:26:17.520 --> 00:26:21.330 align:middle line:84%
And what quantum
physics is saying

00:26:21.330 --> 00:26:27.240 align:middle line:84%
is that so this world exists
in a state of potentiality

00:26:27.240 --> 00:26:31.290 align:middle line:84%
that any possible way this
world can manifest actually

00:26:31.290 --> 00:26:33.930 align:middle line:90%
exists in the potential state.

00:26:33.930 --> 00:26:37.290 align:middle line:84%
And the moment that
any-- and it's unclear

00:26:37.290 --> 00:26:40.200 align:middle line:84%
who the observer is, a person,
or what about an insect,

00:26:40.200 --> 00:26:42.280 align:middle line:84%
or whatever, that's a
whole other question.

00:26:42.280 --> 00:26:46.200 align:middle line:84%
But at the moment
that it's observed,

00:26:46.200 --> 00:26:48.960 align:middle line:84%
those infinite
potentialities collapse

00:26:48.960 --> 00:26:53.850 align:middle line:84%
into particular, actual
manifestation of the 3D world.

00:26:53.850 --> 00:26:57.390 align:middle line:84%
And we're actually, you
know, moment by moment

00:26:57.390 --> 00:27:01.050 align:middle line:84%
playing a part in that process,
but we-- and we're always

00:27:01.050 --> 00:27:03.300 align:middle line:84%
doing it, and we've
always been doing it,

00:27:03.300 --> 00:27:06.480 align:middle line:84%
but we have been doing
it unconsciously.

00:27:06.480 --> 00:27:08.910 align:middle line:84%
So what I'm saying,
you see, you know,

00:27:08.910 --> 00:27:12.210 align:middle line:84%
in quantum physics,
the typical physicist,

00:27:12.210 --> 00:27:13.440 align:middle line:90%
they're not interested.

00:27:13.440 --> 00:27:16.224 align:middle line:84%
They don't-- if you say to them,
well, what about consciousness,

00:27:16.224 --> 00:27:18.390 align:middle line:84%
the typical thing is they'll
just respond by saying,

00:27:18.390 --> 00:27:19.850 align:middle line:90%
shut up and calculate.

00:27:19.850 --> 00:27:20.650 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Exactly.

00:27:20.650 --> 00:27:21.775 align:middle line:90%
>> PAUL: That's the phrase.

00:27:21.775 --> 00:27:24.300 align:middle line:84%
But so here's me, who's just
like a really curious person,

00:27:24.300 --> 00:27:27.570 align:middle line:84%
who's spiritually interested,
and I'm really wanting

00:27:27.570 --> 00:27:29.680 align:middle line:84%
to understand,
well, wait a second,

00:27:29.680 --> 00:27:32.820 align:middle line:84%
here's this thing that sort
of fell from the heavens

00:27:32.820 --> 00:27:35.670 align:middle line:84%
that's-- and we're developing
unbelievable technology.

00:27:35.670 --> 00:27:38.160 align:middle line:84%
It's changed the course
of human history.

00:27:38.160 --> 00:27:41.520 align:middle line:84%
And the physicists who are the
real cutting edge physicists

00:27:41.520 --> 00:27:44.280 align:middle line:84%
are saying that's just
the low hanging fruit.

00:27:44.280 --> 00:27:48.450 align:middle line:84%
That's just like 0.001%
of what it's showing us.

00:27:48.450 --> 00:27:51.040 align:middle line:84%
And so here's me
who's saying, well,

00:27:51.040 --> 00:27:53.940 align:middle line:84%
wait a second, what is
the meaning of the fact

00:27:53.940 --> 00:27:58.320 align:middle line:84%
that this quantum has all of
a sudden come into our world?

00:27:58.320 --> 00:27:59.730 align:middle line:90%
What is that showing us?

00:27:59.730 --> 00:28:02.280 align:middle line:84%
And I guess one other thing
I want to say about that,

00:28:02.280 --> 00:28:05.730 align:middle line:84%
one very famous quantum
physics says, oh, well,

00:28:05.730 --> 00:28:08.040 align:middle line:84%
the thing with-- he's
a very philosophical.

00:28:08.040 --> 00:28:10.200 align:middle line:84%
He says, well, philosophy
is too important

00:28:10.200 --> 00:28:12.360 align:middle line:90%
to be left to the philosophers.

00:28:12.360 --> 00:28:14.730 align:middle line:84%
And so he's very
philosophical in his

00:28:14.730 --> 00:28:16.530 align:middle line:84%
trying to understand
quantum physics.

00:28:16.530 --> 00:28:17.970 align:middle line:84%
Well, I want to
say to him, yeah,

00:28:17.970 --> 00:28:20.510 align:middle line:84%
but physics is too important
to be left to the physicists.

00:28:20.510 --> 00:28:21.310 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: It is.

00:28:21.310 --> 00:28:22.684 align:middle line:84%
>> PAUL: That we
need to really--

00:28:22.684 --> 00:28:23.500 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: It is.

00:28:23.500 --> 00:28:25.920 align:middle line:10%
And I think that's why I love
Michael Talbot's work so much.

00:28:25.920 --> 00:28:26.760 align:middle line:10%
He died young.

00:28:26.760 --> 00:28:27.560 align:middle line:10%
>> PAUL: Right.

00:28:27.560 --> 00:28:31.080 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA: But he understood
where consciousness and physics

00:28:31.080 --> 00:28:32.862 align:middle line:10%
