00:34:38.909 --> 00:34:40.750 align:middle line:90%
but via the medium of science.

00:34:40.750 --> 00:34:42.179 align:middle line:90%
So the thing about quantum--

00:34:42.179 --> 00:34:44.639 align:middle line:84%
you know, the
quantum is that it's

00:34:44.639 --> 00:34:47.580 align:middle line:84%
both it's both pointing
at the dreamlike nature

00:34:47.580 --> 00:34:50.489 align:middle line:84%
and it's an
expression of which it

00:34:50.489 --> 00:34:54.600 align:middle line:84%
is pointing at the same time,
which is to say it's a symbol.

00:34:54.600 --> 00:34:57.790 align:middle line:84%
And symbols, when you
try to figure out,

00:34:57.790 --> 00:34:59.190 align:middle line:90%
oh, how do I work with dreams?

00:34:59.190 --> 00:35:01.320 align:middle line:84%
Well, dreams speak the
language of symbols.

00:35:01.320 --> 00:35:04.290 align:middle line:84%
You know, the symbols
are its language.

00:35:04.290 --> 00:35:07.780 align:middle line:84%
And so quantum physics
is a symbolic procedure.

00:35:07.780 --> 00:35:10.650 align:middle line:84%
And so the thing
I'm trying to say

00:35:10.650 --> 00:35:12.480 align:middle line:84%
is that quantum
physics, it's actually,

00:35:12.480 --> 00:35:15.000 align:middle line:84%
by pointing out the
dreamlike nature,

00:35:15.000 --> 00:35:18.840 align:middle line:84%
when we begin to contemplate
this world and our lives

00:35:18.840 --> 00:35:20.550 align:middle line:84%
as if it's a dream
and understand

00:35:20.550 --> 00:35:24.210 align:middle line:84%
what is it symbolically
showing us, all of a sudden

00:35:24.210 --> 00:35:26.120 align:middle line:84%
we're having an expansion
of consciousness.

00:35:26.120 --> 00:35:26.920 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: We are.

00:35:26.920 --> 00:35:29.100 align:middle line:84%
And in some of the
ancient mysteries,

00:35:29.100 --> 00:35:32.700 align:middle line:84%
it talks about the various
people who incarnated as what

00:35:32.700 --> 00:35:35.250 align:middle line:84%
we call the great masters
throughout history, right,

00:35:35.250 --> 00:35:38.280 align:middle line:90%
and they're-- you can study--

00:35:38.280 --> 00:35:40.290 align:middle line:84%
anyone can research
this themselves.

00:35:40.290 --> 00:35:44.160 align:middle line:84%
But it would be as though
the same motivating force

00:35:44.160 --> 00:35:46.860 align:middle line:84%
or motivating uber
entity even is

00:35:46.860 --> 00:35:50.100 align:middle line:84%
coming in incarnating at
these key periods of times

00:35:50.100 --> 00:35:52.170 align:middle line:84%
through this lineage
of individuals, Buddha

00:35:52.170 --> 00:35:53.380 align:middle line:90%
being one of them.

00:35:53.380 --> 00:35:54.180 align:middle line:90%
>> PAUL: Right.

00:35:54.180 --> 00:35:55.150 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Mithra.

00:35:55.150 --> 00:35:55.950 align:middle line:90%
Jesus.

00:35:55.950 --> 00:35:56.992 align:middle line:90%
Many, many, many of them.

00:35:56.992 --> 00:35:57.908 align:middle line:90%
>> PAUL: Right, right.

00:35:57.908 --> 00:36:00.330 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: At key periods of
time where society is ready

00:36:00.330 --> 00:36:02.677 align:middle line:84%
to be seated with something
that's going to change

00:36:02.677 --> 00:36:04.260 align:middle line:84%
their thoughts,
uplift their thoughts,

00:36:04.260 --> 00:36:05.470 align:middle line:90%
or change their destiny.

00:36:05.470 --> 00:36:06.270 align:middle line:90%
>> PAUL: Right.

00:36:06.270 --> 00:36:07.895 align:middle line:84%
That's absolutely
true, and the thing--

00:36:07.895 --> 00:36:10.350 align:middle line:84%
what that brings to mind for
me is, with quantum physics,

00:36:10.350 --> 00:36:12.840 align:middle line:84%
all the founding
fathers who were saying

00:36:12.840 --> 00:36:15.842 align:middle line:84%
that the real change in
quantum physics that it's

00:36:15.842 --> 00:36:17.800 align:middle line:84%
going to bring in the
world is in our thinking,

00:36:17.800 --> 00:36:18.790 align:middle line:90%
is in our mind.

00:36:18.790 --> 00:36:19.260 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Absolutely.

00:36:19.260 --> 00:36:21.093 align:middle line:84%
>> PAUL: And that, like
I was saying before,

00:36:21.093 --> 00:36:23.760 align:middle line:84%
all the technology and,
you know, it's created,

00:36:23.760 --> 00:36:26.250 align:middle line:84%
according to these quantum
physicists, this is this epoch.

00:36:26.250 --> 00:36:29.220 align:middle line:84%
This is a new epoch
because of quantum physics.

00:36:29.220 --> 00:36:32.520 align:middle line:84%
It's that radical
of a discovery.

00:36:32.520 --> 00:36:36.000 align:middle line:84%
But it's actually,
you know, what

00:36:36.000 --> 00:36:40.200 align:middle line:84%
we've done with it so far is
so minuscule compared to what

00:36:40.200 --> 00:36:41.310 align:middle line:90%
it's actually showing us.

00:36:41.310 --> 00:36:41.670 align:middle line:90%
And what it's showing us--

00:36:41.670 --> 00:36:42.490 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Well, it's
just the beginning.

00:36:42.490 --> 00:36:43.323 align:middle line:90%
>> PAUL: Yeah, yeah.

00:36:43.323 --> 00:36:45.520 align:middle line:84%
Well, because it's such
an over-the-top discovery,

00:36:45.520 --> 00:36:48.870 align:middle line:84%
and when we have discoveries
like this in history,

00:36:48.870 --> 00:36:51.390 align:middle line:84%
they typically take
years and years for us

00:36:51.390 --> 00:36:53.040 align:middle line:84%
to unpack, what is
the meaning of this?

00:36:53.040 --> 00:36:54.600 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: We're coming
out of the industrial age,

00:36:54.600 --> 00:36:55.380 align:middle line:90%
for heaven's sake--

00:36:55.380 --> 00:36:55.680 align:middle line:90%
>> PAUL: Right.

00:36:55.680 --> 00:36:57.530 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: --with soot
covered kids, you know?

00:36:57.530 --> 00:36:58.260 align:middle line:90%
>> PAUL: Right.

00:36:58.260 --> 00:37:00.551 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So yeah, it is
going to take a little while.

00:37:00.551 --> 00:37:03.450 align:middle line:84%
But there is a
particular individual

00:37:03.450 --> 00:37:05.790 align:middle line:84%
that you have great
respect for in this way.

00:37:05.790 --> 00:37:08.040 align:middle line:10%
When we're talking about
great enlightened master

00:37:08.040 --> 00:37:10.650 align:middle line:10%
entities that come to the Earth
to drop certain information

00:37:10.650 --> 00:37:14.000 align:middle line:10%
at a certain time and
shift society's direction,

00:37:14.000 --> 00:37:17.010 align:middle line:10%
might John Archibald
Wheeler be that for you?

00:37:17.010 --> 00:37:18.140 align:middle line:10%
>> PAUL: Oh, totally.

00:37:18.140 --> 00:37:19.120 align:middle line:90%
He really is.

00:37:19.120 --> 00:37:22.560 align:middle line:84%
And I actually-- when I
was a freshman in college,

00:37:22.560 --> 00:37:24.990 align:middle line:84%
I went to visit my best
friend at Princeton

00:37:24.990 --> 00:37:28.290 align:middle line:84%
and he was studying physics,
and I went to his physics,

00:37:28.290 --> 00:37:30.230 align:middle line:84%
you know, the intro
physics class.

00:37:30.230 --> 00:37:33.510 align:middle line:84%
And right before it started, he
leaned over to me and he said,

00:37:33.510 --> 00:37:36.660 align:middle line:84%
(WHISPERING) John Wheeler
is sitting right behind you.

00:37:36.660 --> 00:37:38.580 align:middle line:84%
And I had no idea
who John Wheeler was.

00:37:38.580 --> 00:37:41.220 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I could have touched
him, he was that close.

00:37:41.220 --> 00:37:44.520 align:middle line:84%
And I kind of make a joke now
that, yeah, our wave functions

00:37:44.520 --> 00:37:46.410 align:middle line:84%
got face entangled
in that moment.

00:37:46.410 --> 00:37:50.230 align:middle line:84%
But he was a colleague
of Bohr and Einstein,

00:37:50.230 --> 00:37:53.710 align:middle line:84%
and he was so amazing and
such an inspiration to me.

00:37:53.710 --> 00:37:56.410 align:middle line:10%
I mean, he-- you know, with
my new book, he's the one

00:37:56.410 --> 00:37:57.210 align:middle line:10%
I dedicated it to.

00:37:57.210 --> 00:37:57.730 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:37:57.730 --> 00:37:58.530 align:middle line:10%
>> PAUL: Yeah.

00:37:58.530 --> 00:38:01.080 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA: I mean, not only a
quantum physicist, but a poet.

00:38:01.080 --> 00:38:03.690 align:middle line:84%
He was a thinker of a much
larger nature where he saw

00:38:03.690 --> 00:38:05.305 align:middle line:90%
how all of this came together.

00:38:05.305 --> 00:38:06.180 align:middle line:90%
>> PAUL: Oh, totally.

00:38:06.180 --> 00:38:08.220 align:middle line:90%
And he was open--

00:38:08.220 --> 00:38:10.500 align:middle line:84%
he opened himself to
a lot of criticism

00:38:10.500 --> 00:38:14.160 align:middle line:84%
from the straight physicists
who thought, oh, why

00:38:14.160 --> 00:38:16.200 align:middle line:84%
is he spending so much
time in this really

00:38:16.200 --> 00:38:18.480 align:middle line:90%
out there, this speculation?

00:38:18.480 --> 00:38:20.430 align:middle line:84%
But he was really
trying to understand

00:38:20.430 --> 00:38:23.580 align:middle line:84%
what is the meaning of
the quantum, you know?

00:38:23.580 --> 00:38:30.150 align:middle line:84%
And so he was like this poet
and a philosopher who really

00:38:30.150 --> 00:38:32.850 align:middle line:84%
brought in, you know,
that deeper point

00:38:32.850 --> 00:38:35.820 align:middle line:84%
of view of trying to understand
the philosophical meaning

00:38:35.820 --> 00:38:39.790 align:middle line:84%
of things in a way that
deeply, deeply it speaks to me.

00:38:39.790 --> 00:38:42.570 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So if someone
is wanting to dive into it,

00:38:42.570 --> 00:38:43.827 align:middle line:90%
John Archibald Wheeler?

00:38:43.827 --> 00:38:44.910 align:middle line:90%
>> PAUL: Yeah, yeah, yeah.

00:38:44.910 --> 00:38:45.060 align:middle line:90%
Totally.

00:38:45.060 --> 00:38:45.450 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Go there.

00:38:45.450 --> 00:38:45.945 align:middle line:90%
Go there.

00:38:45.945 --> 00:38:46.778 align:middle line:90%
>> PAUL: Absolutely.

00:38:46.778 --> 00:38:49.450 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And what inspired you
to do your life's work as well.

00:38:49.450 --> 00:38:52.410 align:middle line:84%
And so within this whole
soup of understanding,

00:38:52.410 --> 00:38:54.600 align:middle line:84%
you've come to believe,
you say, that art

00:38:54.600 --> 00:38:56.670 align:middle line:90%
is the queen of all sciences.

00:38:56.670 --> 00:38:59.790 align:middle line:84%
So what is it in the
creative world of art that--

00:38:59.790 --> 00:39:00.610 align:middle line:90%
>> PAUL: Right.

00:39:00.610 --> 00:39:01.410 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:39:01.410 --> 00:39:04.240 align:middle line:90%
Well, the thing is that--

00:39:04.240 --> 00:39:07.740 align:middle line:84%
so here I am not a scientist,
and yet, for decades, I've

00:39:07.740 --> 00:39:10.860 align:middle line:84%
been really just so
fascinated by quantum physics.

00:39:10.860 --> 00:39:13.080 align:middle line:84%
And the more I began to
study quantum physics

00:39:13.080 --> 00:39:15.660 align:middle line:84%
and the more I began to
study the physicists who

00:39:15.660 --> 00:39:18.090 align:middle line:84%
were the founders
of quantum physics,

00:39:18.090 --> 00:39:20.460 align:middle line:84%
the more I began to
understand, oh, they

00:39:20.460 --> 00:39:21.990 align:middle line:84%
were like artists
in that they were

00:39:21.990 --> 00:39:24.390 align:middle line:90%
incredibly creative people.

00:39:24.390 --> 00:39:27.690 align:middle line:84%
And it was through
having an imagination

00:39:27.690 --> 00:39:29.310 align:middle line:84%
and the creative
imagination, which

00:39:29.310 --> 00:39:33.750 align:middle line:84%
is really hooked in to not
just our conscious ego,

00:39:33.750 --> 00:39:36.270 align:middle line:84%
but some higher dimensional
part of ourselves,

00:39:36.270 --> 00:39:38.040 align:middle line:84%
whether you call
it God or whatever,

00:39:38.040 --> 00:39:40.290 align:middle line:84%
that it was through the
creative imagination

00:39:40.290 --> 00:39:43.770 align:middle line:84%
that the greatest discoveries
in physics were being made.

00:39:43.770 --> 00:39:46.590 align:middle line:84%
And so then I began
to realize, well,

00:39:46.590 --> 00:39:50.850 align:middle line:84%
art and science, which typically
are seen to be opposites,

00:39:50.850 --> 00:39:56.460 align:middle line:84%
actually are really so
kind of these complements

00:39:56.460 --> 00:40:00.300 align:middle line:84%
and interrelated
in that they feed--

00:40:00.300 --> 00:40:01.660 align:middle line:90%
they feed each other.

00:40:01.660 --> 00:40:02.460 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: They do.

00:40:02.460 --> 00:40:04.800 align:middle line:84%
And there's also
another component to art

00:40:04.800 --> 00:40:06.720 align:middle line:90%
that science does not possess.

00:40:06.720 --> 00:40:09.540 align:middle line:84%
And as you say, desire
is what drives us forward

00:40:09.540 --> 00:40:10.690 align:middle line:90%
into our creation, right?

00:40:10.690 --> 00:40:11.490 align:middle line:90%
>> PAUL: Mhm.

00:40:11.490 --> 00:40:12.390 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And
this is something--

00:40:12.390 --> 00:40:14.730 align:middle line:84%
and this is where it sometimes
can come into conflict with

00:40:14.730 --> 00:40:15.530 align:middle line:90%
Buddhism.

00:40:15.530 --> 00:40:18.400 align:middle line:84%
Desire is the root of all
suffering is one axiom, right?

00:40:18.400 --> 00:40:21.430 align:middle line:84%
But on the other hand,
desire's what moves us forward

00:40:21.430 --> 00:40:24.400 align:middle line:84%
into everything we create
on one level or another.

00:40:24.400 --> 00:40:28.060 align:middle line:84%
Art can create an
incredible kind of desire

00:40:28.060 --> 00:40:29.232 align:middle line:90%
within for experience.

00:40:29.232 --> 00:40:31.690 align:middle line:84%
>> PAUL: And I think that that
contradiction with Buddhism,

00:40:31.690 --> 00:40:35.320 align:middle line:84%
that's just a question of like
semantics in the sense that,

00:40:35.320 --> 00:40:38.180 align:middle line:90%
for me, you know, for--

00:40:38.180 --> 00:40:41.080 align:middle line:84%
if somebody who's
not a physicist,

00:40:41.080 --> 00:40:42.850 align:middle line:84%
they wanna understand
what is the takeaway

00:40:42.850 --> 00:40:45.400 align:middle line:84%
from this conversation
or from my book,

00:40:45.400 --> 00:40:51.070 align:middle line:84%
is that we are these
incredibly creative beings.

00:40:51.070 --> 00:40:55.390 align:middle line:84%
And what most of us
unfortunately have done

00:40:55.390 --> 00:40:58.250 align:middle line:90%
is we've been entrained--

00:40:58.250 --> 00:41:02.080 align:middle line:84%
we've actually, in a
way, hypnotized ourselves

00:41:02.080 --> 00:41:06.010 align:middle line:84%
so that our creativity turns
against us in a way that's

00:41:06.010 --> 00:41:09.580 align:middle line:84%
like this limiting way
that's basically killing us,

00:41:09.580 --> 00:41:12.550 align:middle line:84%
and that's actually
playing out in the body

00:41:12.550 --> 00:41:13.434 align:middle line:90%
politic of the world.

00:41:13.434 --> 00:41:14.350 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Absolutely.

00:41:14.350 --> 00:41:14.680 align:middle line:90%
>> PAUL: You know?

00:41:14.680 --> 00:41:16.055 align:middle line:84%
And when you see
this as a dream,

00:41:16.055 --> 00:41:18.880 align:middle line:84%
you understand that
what's playing out there

00:41:18.880 --> 00:41:20.680 align:middle line:84%
in the external
dimension is actually

00:41:20.680 --> 00:41:23.170 align:middle line:84%
a reflection, just
like a dream, of what's

00:41:23.170 --> 00:41:25.810 align:middle line:90%
happening inside of our psyche.

00:41:25.810 --> 00:41:29.140 align:middle line:84%
And so yeah, so the thing
about quantum physics

00:41:29.140 --> 00:41:32.110 align:middle line:84%
is that it's really
not just pointing

00:41:32.110 --> 00:41:35.680 align:middle line:84%
at that we're creative beings,
but when you begin to really go

00:41:35.680 --> 00:41:37.750 align:middle line:84%
down the rabbit hole
of quantum physics,

00:41:37.750 --> 00:41:41.380 align:middle line:84%
it actually unlocks
that infinite creativity

00:41:41.380 --> 00:41:44.680 align:middle line:84%
that we have access to
each and every moment,

00:41:44.680 --> 00:41:48.050 align:middle line:84%
but like I was saying before,
we're just unconscious of that.

00:41:48.050 --> 00:41:51.330 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And going back,
I'm a big one on desire,

00:41:51.330 --> 00:41:54.817 align:middle line:84%
that these kinds of heartfelt,
gut felt generated desires,

00:41:54.817 --> 00:41:57.400 align:middle line:84%
even on the part of the artist,
that's what pulls them forward

00:41:57.400 --> 00:42:00.080 align:middle line:84%
into their creation, it's what
pulls us forward into our own

00:42:00.080 --> 00:42:00.880 align:middle line:90%
creation.

00:42:00.880 --> 00:42:01.270 align:middle line:90%
>> PAUL: Right.

00:42:01.270 --> 00:42:03.610 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Sometimes it
can be incredibly beautiful

00:42:03.610 --> 00:42:04.450 align:middle line:90%
and fruitful.

00:42:04.450 --> 00:42:06.400 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes it can be
very destructive.

00:42:06.400 --> 00:42:09.730 align:middle line:84%
Either way, it has a very
powerful effect of drawing out

00:42:09.730 --> 00:42:13.090 align:middle line:84%
a creation, and one of them
is prediction and control

00:42:13.090 --> 00:42:17.260 align:middle line:84%
that we're seeing really
as the illness in society

00:42:17.260 --> 00:42:18.700 align:middle line:90%
today on a lot of levels.

00:42:18.700 --> 00:42:21.500 align:middle line:84%
But you say, in general,
prediction and control is dead,

00:42:21.500 --> 00:42:22.300 align:middle line:90%
in your book.

00:42:22.300 --> 00:42:22.640 align:middle line:90%
>> PAUL: Yeah, yeah, yeah.

00:42:22.640 --> 00:42:23.800 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Let's talk about
what do you mean by that.

00:42:23.800 --> 00:42:24.600 align:middle line:90%
>> PAUL: Totally.

00:42:24.600 --> 00:42:27.040 align:middle line:84%
What I meant by that is
that, before quantum physics,

00:42:27.040 --> 00:42:30.400 align:middle line:84%
physicists thought that if
they had enough information,

00:42:30.400 --> 00:42:33.760 align:middle line:84%
they could predict the future,
and that it was deterministic,

00:42:33.760 --> 00:42:36.850 align:middle line:90%
it was this mechanistic system.

00:42:36.850 --> 00:42:41.350 align:middle line:84%
And-- but quantum physics
has shown that, no, no, no,

00:42:41.350 --> 00:42:45.610 align:middle line:84%
you know, the idea of prediction
that that's an old idea that

00:42:45.610 --> 00:42:48.670 align:middle line:84%
everything is in a state
you can actually predict

00:42:48.670 --> 00:42:51.310 align:middle line:84%
the probability of,
well, this is, you know,

00:42:51.310 --> 00:42:53.950 align:middle line:84%
99% probable that
this will happen,

00:42:53.950 --> 00:42:56.200 align:middle line:90%
but you can't say for sure--

00:42:56.200 --> 00:42:58.940 align:middle line:84%
for sure, for definite
sure that what,

00:42:58.940 --> 00:43:00.430 align:middle line:84%
you know, what's
going to happen.

00:43:00.430 --> 00:43:03.460 align:middle line:84%
And that opens up
vistas of possibilities.

00:43:03.460 --> 00:43:06.670 align:middle line:84%
Because say if,
for example, there

00:43:06.670 --> 00:43:10.990 align:middle line:84%
is a minutely small possibility
that we, as a species,

00:43:10.990 --> 00:43:13.150 align:middle line:84%
might wake up, right,
and might wake up

00:43:13.150 --> 00:43:16.377 align:middle line:84%
and connect with each other
and change this waking dream.

00:43:16.377 --> 00:43:17.960 align:middle line:84%
Well, quantum physics
is saying, well,

00:43:17.960 --> 00:43:20.350 align:middle line:84%
wait a second, that's
a possibility, right?

00:43:20.350 --> 00:43:23.220 align:middle line:84%
That means that that
actually could manifest.

00:43:23.220 --> 00:43:24.020 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:43:24.020 --> 00:43:26.350 align:middle line:84%
>> PAUL: And that,
all of a sudden--

00:43:26.350 --> 00:43:28.930 align:middle line:84%
you see, because if we hold
like this pessimistic viewpoint

00:43:28.930 --> 00:43:30.250 align:middle line:90%
of like, oh, no, no, no--

00:43:30.250 --> 00:43:31.180 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: It's going to
hell in a hand basket.

00:43:31.180 --> 00:43:33.054 align:middle line:84%
>> PAUL: It's going to
