guys are saying.

00:44:21.700 --> 00:44:23.740 align:middle line:84%
And not just guys,
there are also women.

00:44:23.740 --> 00:44:26.470 align:middle line:84%
But the idea-- what
they're-- one of the things

00:44:26.470 --> 00:44:30.580 align:middle line:84%
they're saying is that the
importance of don't take

00:44:30.580 --> 00:44:33.280 align:middle line:90%
anybody else's word for it.

00:44:33.280 --> 00:44:35.210 align:middle line:84%
Take-- you know,
think for yourself.

00:44:35.210 --> 00:44:36.010 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:44:36.010 --> 00:44:36.850 align:middle line:90%
>> PAUL: Do the experiments.

00:44:36.850 --> 00:44:39.484 align:middle line:84%
Just like the Buddha said, the
Buddha was giving teachings

00:44:39.484 --> 00:44:41.650 align:middle line:84%
and he said to-- he literally
said to his disciples,

00:44:41.650 --> 00:44:42.850 align:middle line:90%
don't take my word for it--

00:44:42.850 --> 00:44:43.360 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Exactly.

00:44:43.360 --> 00:44:45.070 align:middle line:84%
>> PAUL: --do the
experiment yourself.

00:44:45.070 --> 00:44:47.330 align:middle line:84%
Go within and see if
what I'm saying is true.

00:44:47.330 --> 00:44:49.750 align:middle line:84%
And that's exactly what the
quantum physicists are saying.

00:44:49.750 --> 00:44:52.870 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: As all great
teachers, from kindergarten up,

00:44:52.870 --> 00:44:53.890 align:middle line:90%
will do.

00:44:53.890 --> 00:44:54.870 align:middle line:90%
Try it.

00:44:54.870 --> 00:44:56.840 align:middle line:90%
See-- see what you can do.

00:44:56.840 --> 00:45:01.030 align:middle line:84%
See where your mind can
do and create for you.

00:45:01.030 --> 00:45:03.490 align:middle line:84%
That's the mark of a
responsible, real teacher,

00:45:03.490 --> 00:45:06.430 align:middle line:84%
whether it's on a universal
level or in kindergarten.

00:45:06.430 --> 00:45:08.020 align:middle line:84%
And oftentimes,
instead we're being

00:45:08.020 --> 00:45:10.450 align:middle line:84%
stuffed with what's right,
what's wrong, you know,

00:45:10.450 --> 00:45:11.870 align:middle line:90%
memorization, and so forth.

00:45:11.870 --> 00:45:14.750 align:middle line:84%
And this is, again, an extension
of that old industrial age

00:45:14.750 --> 00:45:15.550 align:middle line:90%
remnant--

00:45:15.550 --> 00:45:20.010 align:middle line:84%
dying remnant of what we would
call a patriarchal overlay

00:45:20.010 --> 00:45:21.090 align:middle line:90%
to our psychology.

00:45:21.090 --> 00:45:22.030 align:middle line:84%
>> PAUL: Oh, that's
definitely true.

00:45:22.030 --> 00:45:23.946 align:middle line:84%
And the thing is is what
you were just saying,

00:45:23.946 --> 00:45:26.280 align:middle line:84%
it made me think
that this other thing

00:45:26.280 --> 00:45:28.230 align:middle line:84%
that these great
physics are saying,

00:45:28.230 --> 00:45:30.180 align:middle line:84%
they're saying
way more important

00:45:30.180 --> 00:45:34.304 align:middle line:84%
than finding the right answer
