>> PAUL: Right.

00:46:21.470 --> 00:46:24.480 align:middle line:84%
So the polishing,
you know, that--

00:46:24.480 --> 00:46:26.040 align:middle line:84%
you know, that
precious jewel, it's

00:46:26.040 --> 00:46:29.390 align:middle line:84%
like there's a metaphor in
spiritual traditions of Indra's

00:46:29.390 --> 00:46:30.190 align:middle line:90%
net.

00:46:30.190 --> 00:46:34.560 align:middle line:10%
And Indra's net is this net
of these polished-- like these

00:46:34.560 --> 00:46:37.470 align:middle line:10%
gemstones, these
jewels at each them,

00:46:37.470 --> 00:46:40.740 align:middle line:10%
where all where the threads
intersect, and they all

00:46:40.740 --> 00:46:43.270 align:middle line:10%
are-- they reflect each other.

00:46:43.270 --> 00:46:45.480 align:middle line:84%
So in any jewel, all
the other jewels,

00:46:45.480 --> 00:46:47.680 align:middle line:84%
which goes on to
infinity, are reflected.

00:46:47.680 --> 00:46:48.480 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:46:48.480 --> 00:46:51.030 align:middle line:84%
>> PAUL: And-- but the
point is, so those--

00:46:51.030 --> 00:46:54.210 align:middle line:84%
each of those jewels, you
know, one could think of them

00:46:54.210 --> 00:46:56.160 align:middle line:84%
as being, oh, they're
each one of us.

00:46:56.160 --> 00:46:58.380 align:middle line:84%
